Below is a complete, self-contained HTML file that visualizes a singly linked list. It includes:

- **Visualization**: Nodes are represented as boxes, connected by arrows (using text-based arrows for simplicity).
- **Controls**:
  - Insert at head: Adds a new node at the beginning of the list.
  - Insert at tail: Adds a new node at the end of the list.
  - Delete by value: Removes the first occurrence of a node with the specified value.
  - Search: Highlights the first node with the specified value (if found).
- **Empty List Handling**: If the list is empty, it displays a message like "The list is empty."
- **Interactivity**: All operations update the visualization in real-time.

The file includes embedded CSS for styling and JavaScript for the linked list logic and DOM updates. I've kept it simple, user-friendly, and responsive.

Here's the full HTML file. You can copy and paste it into a text editor, save it as `linked_list.html`, and open it in a web browser to interact with it.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Singly Linked List Visualizer</title>
    <style>
        /* Basic styling for the page */
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
        }

        #controls {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        #controls input, #controls button {
            padding: 8px;
            margin-right: 10px;
            font-size: 14px;
        }

        #list-container {
            display: flex;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 10px;
            padding: 10px;
            background-color: #fff;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }

        .node {
            background-color: lightblue;
            padding: 10px 15px;
            border: 1px solid #007bff;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-weight: bold;
            position: relative;
            min-width: 50px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .highlighted {
            background-color: yellow; /* Highlight for searched node */
            border-color: orange;
        }

        /* Empty list message */
        .empty-message {
            color: #666;
            font-style: italic;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Singly Linked List Visualizer</h1>
    <div id="controls">
        <input type="text" id="valueInput" placeholder="Enter a value (e.g., 1)">
        <button id="insertHead">Insert at Head</button>
        <button id="insertTail">Insert at Tail</button>
        <button id="deleteValue">Delete by Value</button>
        <button id="searchValue">Search</button>
    </div>
    <div id="list-container">
        <!-- The list will be rendered here -->
        <p class="empty-message">The list is empty.</p>
    </div>

    <script>
        // Linked List Implementation
        class Node {
            constructor(value) {
                this.value = value;
                this.next = null;
            }
        }

        class LinkedList {
            constructor() {
                this.head = null;
            }

            insertHead(value) {
                const newNode = new Node(value);
                newNode.next = this.head;
                this.head = newNode;
            }

            insertTail(value) {
                const newNode = new Node(value);
                if (!this.head) {
                    this.head = newNode;
                    return;
                }
                let current = this.head;
                while (current.next) {
                    current = current.next;
                }
                current.next = newNode;
            }

            deleteByValue(value) {
                if (!this.head) return; // Empty list
                if (this.head.value === value) {
                    this.head = this.head.next;
                    return;
                }
                let current = this.head;
                while (current.next) {
                    if (current.next.value === value) {
                        current.next = current.next.next;
                        return;
                    }
                    current = current.next;
                }
            }

            search(value) {
                let current = this.head;
                while (current) {
                    if (current.value === value) {
                        return current; // Return the node if found
                    }
                    current = current.next;
                }
                return null; // Not found
            }

            toArray() {
                const arr = [];
                let current = this.head;
                while (current) {
                    arr.push(current.value);
                    current = current.next;
                }
                return arr;
            }
        }

        // Initialize the linked list
        const list = new LinkedList();
        const listContainer = document.getElementById('list-container');
        const emptyMessage = listContainer.querySelector('.empty-message');

        function renderList(highlightValue = null) {
            const values = list.toArray();
            listContainer.innerHTML = ''; // Clear the container

            if (values.length === 0) {
                emptyMessage.style.display = 'block'; // Show empty message
                return;
            }

            emptyMessage.style.display = 'none'; // Hide empty message

            values.forEach((value, index) => {
                const nodeDiv = document.createElement('div');
                nodeDiv.className = 'node';
                if (value === highlightValue) {
                    nodeDiv.classList.add('highlighted'); // Add highlight class
                }
                nodeDiv.textContent = value; // Set the node's value
                if (index < values.length - 1) {
                    nodeDiv.textContent += ' →'; // Add arrow for all except the last
                }
                listContainer.appendChild(nodeDiv);
            });
        }

        // Event listeners for buttons
        document.getElementById('insertHead').addEventListener('click', () => {
            const value = document.getElementById('valueInput').value.trim();
            if (value) {
                list.insertHead(value);
                renderList(); // Re-render without highlight
                document.getElementById('valueInput').value = ''; // Clear input
            } else {
                alert('Please enter a value.');
            }
        });

        document.getElementById('insertTail').addEventListener('click', () => {
            const value = document.getElementById('valueInput').value.trim();
            if (value) {
                list.insertTail(value);
                renderList(); // Re-render without highlight
                document.getElementById('valueInput').value = ''; // Clear input
            } else {
                alert('Please enter a value.');
            }
        });

        document.getElementById('deleteValue').addEventListener('click', () => {
            const value = document.getElementById('valueInput').value.trim();
            if (value) {
                list.deleteByValue(value);
                renderList(); // Re-render without highlight
                document.getElementById('valueInput').value = ''; // Clear input
            } else {
                alert('Please enter a value.');
            }
        });

        document.getElementById('searchValue').addEventListener('click', () => {
            const value = document.getElementById('valueInput').value.trim();
            if (value) {
                const foundNode = list.search(value);
                if (foundNode) {
                    renderList(value); // Re-render with highlight
                } else {
                    alert('Value not found in the list.');
                    renderList(); // Re-render without highlight
                }
                document.getElementById('valueInput').value = ''; // Clear input
            } else {
                alert('Please enter a value.');
            }
        });

        // Initial render
        renderList();
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### How to Use:
1. Open the file in a web browser.
2. Enter a value in the input field (e.g., "5").
3. Click the buttons to perform operations:
   - **Insert at Head**: Adds the value at the start (e.g., the list becomes [5 → ...]).
   - **Insert at Tail**: Adds the value at the end.
   - **Delete by Value**: Removes the first node with that value.
   - **Search**: Highlights the first matching node in yellow.
4. The visualization updates automatically after each action.
5. If the list is empty, you'll see the message "The list is empty."

### Notes:
- **Assumptions**: Values are treated as strings for simplicity, but you can modify the code if needed (e.g., to handle numbers specifically).
- **Edge Cases Handled**:
  - Empty list: Gracefully shows a message.
  - Invalid input: Alerts the user to enter a value.
  - Multiple nodes with the same value: Search highlights only the first one; delete removes only the first occurrence.
- **Visuals**: Nodes are styled as blue boxes with arrows (e.g., "5 → 3 →"). This is a basic implementation; you can enhance it with CSS for more advanced visuals like SVG arrows if desired.
- **Limitations**: This is a simple in-memory implementation. It doesn't persist data across page reloads.

