Below is a complete, self-contained HTML file that visualizes a singly linked list. It includes:

- **Visualization**: Nodes are represented as boxes (using DIV elements), connected by arrows (using CSS and Unicode characters for simplicity).
- **Controls**:
  - **Insert at Head**: Adds a new node at the beginning of the list.
  - **Insert at Tail**: Adds a new node at the end of the list.
  - **Delete by Value**: Removes the first occurrence of a node with the specified value.
  - **Search**: Highlights the first node with the specified value (if found).
- **Empty List Handling**: If the list is empty, it displays a message like "The list is empty." Operations on an empty list are handled gracefully (e.g., no errors, just appropriate messages).
- **Interactivity**: Uses JavaScript to manage the linked list data structure and update the visualization dynamically.

This file is fully functional and can be opened directly in a web browser. I've kept the code clean, commented, and user-friendly.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Singly Linked List Visualizer</title>
    <style>
        /* Basic styling for the page */
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
        }

        /* Container for the linked list visualization */
        #list-container {
            margin: 20px 0;
            padding: 10px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            background-color: #fff;
            min-height: 100px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
        }

